Jack is a college student, and here are his weekly plans: 
(1)On Wednesday, Jack has a group meeting; 
(2)On Wednesday, Jack goes jogging; 
(3)Jack cleans his dormitory room 1 day after he has a group meeting; 
(4)1 day after Jack goes jogging, he reads sci-fi novels; 
(5)1 day after Jack cleans his dormitory room, he practices the guitar; 
(6)On Sunday, Jack watches a movie.
Jack cleans his dormitory room 6 days after ____.
A: Jack watches a movie	B: Jack has a group meeting	C: Jack goes jogging	D: Jack practices the guitar

Jack's daughter is telling her friends about the story of her father's life: 
(1)Jack started elementary school 74 years before IBM released the first personal computer; 
(2)Jack studied in elementary school and spent 6 years on it; 
(3)Jack started dating 65 years before IBM released the first personal computer; 
(4)The total duration that Jack was in a romantic relationship is 9 years longer than he studied in university; 
(5)Jack started university 9 years before bubble gum was invented; 
(6)Jack graduated from university 21 years before the United Nations was founded; 
(7)Jack got married 68 years before Google was founded; 
(8)Jack became a father 60 years before Google was founded; 
(9)Jack retired 19 years after the United Nations was founded.
The gap between the time ____ and the time the United Nations was founded is 17 years.
A: Jack retired	B: IBM released the first personal computer	C: Jack became a father	D: bubble gum was invented

小明是一名大学生，以下是他的每周安排: 
(1)在星期三，他打羽毛球; 
(2)在星期三，他开组会; 
(3)在星期三，他跑步; 
(4)在周四，他整理宿舍; 
(5)在他整理宿舍之后1天，他约会; 
(6)在他跑步之后2天，他练习吉他。
在____之后6天，他开组会。
A: 他练习吉他	B: 他打羽毛球	C: 他跑步	D: 他整理宿舍
